For cost savings, you might consider asking a neighbor for some of their bay leaves or rosemary. Also consider buying dried herbs (expensive but then you have them on hand to use later)
 and substituting with 1/3 quantity--just make sure to give them time to share their flavor.  Also some stores sell bulk herbs where you can purchase small quantities.

@C. Hughes this is not the first cornbread recipe published here
Do a search - you will be surprised, and maybe bemused by the inevitable fight of sugar or not, too sweet or not, bread or cake…
It’s beloved and for me, an immigrant, one of the best things in American cuisine.

@Jackie You put the pie in its pie plate on top of a cookie sheet, because there’s too much filling— I put some in a separate custard cup, but the main pie still overflowed and burnt onto the cookie sheet and was hard to clean.

My pie dishes are made of glass (not pyrex).  I’m pretty sure if I had gone directly from the freezer to a 450 degree oven, it would have shattered.  I just put it in from  room temp to 350 degree oven.  The crust turned out fine.

The author sure loves this pie and gushes over how great it is and its meaning in their life/career, but more attention to the actual recipe would have been good,  IMNSHO.
